30
{
  name { Entrance to Tollerin.  }
  desc {
"   This is the entrance to a small forest village. Thick bamboo has
been entwined with vines to form a sturdy fence, acting to keep 
wild animals out. A large oak sign has been picketed into the ground
and reads, 'Welcome to Tollerin!' It seems to be a pleasant little town,
the children play merrily to the north, the locals eye you over with a 
look of concern.
  }
  extra {
	keywords { sign }
	desc { 
This is a large oak sign which has been hammered deep into the ground. It reads,
'Welcome to Tollerin!'
	}
  }
  flags { no_sum }
  exits {
	to { n, 31 }
  }
}

31
{
  name { Central Square.  }
  desc {
"  This is a very dirty and unkept central square. Locals walk silently
around the edges of the square, many careful not to approach the
large statue which occupies the center. Mothers slap the wrists of 
children attempting to approach the statue, cursing them out and 
pulling them away quickly.
  }
  extra {
	keywords { large statue }
	desc { 
This is a large statue of a slight man, dressed in leather clothing and carrying a sharp dagger.
His face is hidden by a black hood, which has purposely been pulled over his face. Words are
engraved at the base of the statue on a brass slab.
	}
	keywords { brass slab }
	desc {  It reads, 'In memory of Twindle Slightfingers, founder of Tollerin.' 	}
  }
  flags { no_sum }
  exits {
	to { n, 36 }
	to { e, 34 }
	to { s, 30 }
	to { w, 33 }
	to { 10, 32 }
	  keywords { weaponsmith }
	to { 11, 35 }
	  keywords { bakery }
  }
}

32
{
  name { A Filthy Weaponsmith.  }
  desc {
"   This small weapons shoppe is quite dark, and it becomes difficult to
make out the scattered metals on the floor.  Most of the items here
appear to be useless.  A large metal table sits in the middle of the room,
obviously for the forging of new weapons.
  }
  extra {
	keywords { table }
	desc {  The table is well worn, and is blackened from the hot metal. 	}
  }
  flags { indoors }
  exits {
	to { 10, 31 }
	  keywords { square }
  }
}

33
{
  name { A Strange Playground.  }
  desc {
"   This is a strange little playground. The children race back and forth
in front of you, trying to catch your attention as others brush quickly 
against your money pouch. There are several ropes tied onto a tree, 
for the children to learn to climb. In the far corner of the playground, 
a maze of chain link has been locked together, with some of the finest
locks you have ever seen. Several children work vigorously with small
tools, trying to pick the various locks.
  }
  extra {
	keywords { rope }
	desc { 
This is a long rope measuring approximately twenty feet long. The children appear to have no
problems mastering their climbing skills.
	}
	keywords { maze chain link }
	desc { 
Quite a strange contraption. There must be a hundred chains, and just as many locks. A few
of the smaller locks have been opened and discarded in a pile. Many of the children work
diligently, driving, poking, and picking at the locks with small silver utensils.
	}
  }
  flags { no_sum }
  exits {
	to { e, 31 }
  }
}

34
{
  name { Rows of Houses.  }
  desc {
"   On this small street is a row of approximately twenty small houses.
The houses windows have been tightly barred with iron, each door
held closed with elaborate locking systems. It is strange that each 
each home is locked so securly, the town seems like a safe and 
friendly place. The central square can be seen to the west.
  }
  flags { no_sum }
  exits {
	to { w, 31 }
  }
}

35
{
  name { An Unkept Bakery.  }
  desc {
"   This place is filthy for a bakery! Stale and rotten bread dough
litters the floor, emitting a rotten, yeasty odour. Several small mice
scurry about, picking up crumbs and fleeing into a small hole in the
wall. A single burnt loaf of bread has been left on the counter, a 
black fly encircles, stopping periodically to feed on the crust.
  }
  extra {
	keywords { loaf bread }
	desc { 
This bread seems to have been here for a very long time. The crust is black and has hardened
over time. Its impossible to tell if it was white or whole wheat, but that doesn't matter,
nobody in their right mind would eat this bread.
	}
	keywords { hole mouse }
	desc { 
This is a small hole in the wall where the mice apparently live. It doesn't seem to
lead to anywhere important.
	}
  }
  flags { indoors }
  exits {
	to { 10, 31 }
	  keywords { square }
  }
}

36
{
  name { An Obscure Path.  }
  desc {
"  This is a dark, unkept forested path. Trees and twigs crack in the
woods on both sides, as though someone is attempting to hide in the
brush. Thorned vines enclose the sides of the path, tugging at 
adventurers equipment like little hands. A small building with a tattered 
 sign lies to the north. The view to the south is obstructed by low 
hanging limbs.
  }
  extra {
	keywords { sign }
	desc {  The sign simply reads, 'INN' 	}
  }
  flags { no_sum }
  exits {
	to { s, 31 }
	to { 10, 37 }
	  keywords { inn }
  }
}

37
{
  name { A Tiny Inn.  }
  desc {
"   This is a very small inn consisting of a tiny entrance, and a barred
office window, where customers can talk to the receptionist. Some
of the bars on the office window have been slightly filed, and scraped
with a sharp tool. Looking in the window, reveals a receptionist, who
looks at you with a hint of distrust. The exit from the inn leads onto an
obscure path.
  }
  flags { indoors, peaceful, rent_room }
  exits {
	to { 10, 36 }
	  keywords { path }
  }
}

